So we ordered food through grubhub ... Only half our food got delivered. We called and spoke with a woman at flagship and she said they don't have the items we ordered and nothing they can do and that we should contact grubhub.  So basically their menu that's on grubhub isn't correct and has many items that they don't even sell at their restaurant.  We called back again and i asked for clarification about why we paid for two soups and sandwich that they don't carry and we didn't receive.  Luckily this unfriendly woman on the phone at Flagship got another employee named Hailey who decided to actually help us.  She told us to contact grub hub and they would call them and give us a refund for the meal.   In the end it handled but it took two phone calls to get someone to care about what happened.

I'm not a huge fan of sportsbars, but I just couldn't give Flagship four stars just because of my bias. Here's why Flagship earned a 5 star from me:  Service: The manager always comes out to greet us. Granted, they are sponsoring our soccer team, but KP always makes a point to come over to chat with us about our game and how they're doing that day. It makes a huge difference; their team discount and drink deals will keep us coming back.  Food: Above par. The mac & cheese with caramelized onions rocked my world. The quesadillas come with guacamole AND a pico de gallo with a kick. I'm also impressed that there are some unique menu offerings like gorgonzola pear burger and an avocado margarita. Pretty creative, if you ask me.  Environment: I'll just say that I've seen a lot of attractive people here and leave it at that. Did I mention that the Real World Chicago cast recently made an appearance here??  Flagship is accommodating for large groups, has a fun atmosphere, and has all your favorite foods made to order. Go!
